\int \dfrac{x-2}{x^2 -4x + 8}\,dx
u = x^2 - 4x + 8 \implies \,du = 2x - 4 = 2(x-2)\,dx \iff \frac 12 du = x - 2 \,dx
\begin{align} \int \dfrac{x-2}{x^2 -4x + 8}\,dx & = \int \frac{\frac 12 \,du}{u} \\ \\ & = \frac 12 \int \frac {du}{u} \\ \\ & = \frac 12 \ln|u| + C =\frac 12 \ln|x^2 - 4x + 8| + C\tag{1}\end{align}
\int\dfrac{1}{\frac{1}{4} (x-2)^2 +1}\,dx = \int \dfrac{1}{\left(\frac 12(x-2)\right)^2 + 1} \,dx
u = \frac 12(x - 2) \implies du = \frac 12 dx \implies 2 du = dx
\begin{align} \int\dfrac{1}{\left(\frac 12(x-2)\right)^2 + 1} \,dx & = \int \frac 1{u^2 + 1}\cdot(2\,du)  \\ \\ & = 2 \int \cdot \dfrac{1}{u^2 + 1} \,du \\ \\& = 2\arctan\left(u\right) + C \\ \\ & = 2 \arctan\left(\frac 12(x - 2)\right) + C \tag{2} \end{align}
