x^2-4x+8=u,2(x-2)dx=du\implies (x-2)dx=\frac{du}2
\int \dfrac{x-2}{x^2-4x+8}=\frac12\cdot\int \frac{du}u=\frac12\cdot\ln|u|+C=\frac12\cdot\ln|x^2-4x+8|+C
x-2=2\tan\theta\implies dx=2\sec^2\theta d\theta
\frac1{(x-2)^2+2^2},
\int \frac{dx}{(x-2)^2+2^2}=\int\frac{2\sec^2\theta d\theta}{4\sec^2\theta}=\frac12\cdot\theta+K=\frac12\cdot\arctan\left(\frac{x-2}2\right)+K
